The paper proposes a method for improving the reliability of confidence estimates from predictive models, which is a common problem in machine learning. The method involves using a flexible yet tractable distribution over discretized latent variables, which is a technique commonly used in deep latent variable models. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of non-linearities, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the scalability and efficiency of the proposed method, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Computation and Language (cs.CL).
